# Deploy-time content bundle.
#
# `data/bundle/blobs/*` are PNG/FBX/OBJ bytes pre-extracted from the
# Project Aegis repo at bake time. A mid-size Aegisgram deploy easily
# hits a few hundred MB across hundreds of files, which pushes the repo
# past GitHub's 100 MB per-file hard limit and makes `git clone` painful
# regardless. Storing these through Git LFS keeps the working tree small
# while the platform's deploy step just needs `git lfs pull` to
# materialize the real bytes.
#
# Pre-baked scene JSONs are plain text but can be 10+ MB each for large
# maps, so we track them via LFS too — no diff value anyway, they're
# regenerated by `npm run bake`.
#
# The manifest itself is a small human-readable JSON that changes every
# bake; keep it as a normal tracked file so PR diffs show bake metadata.

data/bundle/blobs/**         filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
data/bundle/scenes/**        filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
data/bundle/fbx-materials/** filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
